      <result class="- topic/section task/result ">It is possible to configure the batter capacity test to discharge
to a set capacity or for a set duration. In addition it can also be
done with fixed current or fixed power.<p class="- topic/p ">The available settings are:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Capacity</uicontrol>: The battery
is discharged until a set capacity, variable current and variable
power.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Capacity with fixed current</uicontrol>: A The battery is discharged until a set capacity, fixed current
and variable power.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Capacity with fixed power</uicontrol>: The battery is discharged until a set capacity, variable current
and fixed power.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Support time</uicontrol>: The battery
is discharged for a set duration with variable current and variable
power.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Support time with fixed current</uicontrol>: The battery is discharged for a set duration with fixed current
and variable power.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Support time with fixed power</uicontrol>: The battery is discharged for a set duration with variable current
and fixed power.</p>
               </li>
            </ul>If the cell voltage is above the abort voltage until the set
capacity warning level is reached or the set duration have elapsed
the battery capacity test is successful. If the battery cell voltage
at any time does not stay above the abort voltage, the test is interrupted
and considered unsuccessful.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">To check the settings navigate
to <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Service &gt; PRIME &gt; Battery tests</uicontrol> while logged in as a user with <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Service</uicontrol> access.</p>
